---
import HomeworkPage from './product/HomeworkPage.astro';
---

<section id="probe" class="section section-y">
  <div class="container-page">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-start">
      <div class="lg:col-span-5">
        <p class="eyebrow">Between hints</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4 font-serif text-display-2 text-ink-900 leading-[1.05]">
          First, you think.<br />
          The hint <span class="accent-italic">follows</span>.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-6 text-ink-600 text-[16.5px] leading-[1.65]">
          Between hints, Siko pauses and shows dashed boxes around
          each line of the student&rsquo;s work. They tap the step they want to look
          back at &mdash; or type it.
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-7 space-y-4 text-[15px] text-ink-700">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="font-mono text-sage mt-0.5">✓</span>
            <span><strong class="text-ink-900 font-medium">Tap the right step.</strong>
              The next hint comes with <em class="not-italic font-mono text-[13px] text-sage">&ldquo;you&rsquo;re looking in the right place&rdquo;</em>.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="font-mono text-terra mt-0.5">↗</span>
            <span><strong class="text-ink-900 font-medium">Tap a different step.</strong>
              A soft orange ring marks your tap, and the next hint redirects:
              <em class="not-italic font-mono text-[13px] text-terra">&ldquo;look here instead&rdquo;</em>.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="font-mono text-dusty mt-0.5">◎</span>
            <span><strong class="text-ink-900 font-medium">Or type it.</strong>
              &ldquo;the part where I multiplied 5&rdquo; works just as well as a tap.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-8 text-ink-500 text-[14.5px] leading-[1.65] max-w-[44ch]">
          Why this exists: handing out hints without any diagnostic work from
          the student makes them dependent on the hints. Asking
          <em>which step?</em> makes them re-read their own work first &mdash; which
          is the whole point of homework.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="lg:col-span-7">
        <div class="probe-scene">
          <HomeworkPage showProbeTargets={true} />
          {/* A small floating prompt that overlays the homework — mirrors
              the probe section that appears inside the hint card. */}
          <div class="probe-prompt">
            <div class="prompt-q">
              Before the next hint &mdash; which step do you want to look back at?
            </div>
            <div class="prompt-hint">(Tap any step in your work)</div>
            <div class="prompt-links">
              <span class="link-mute">or type instead</span>
              <span class="link-mute">just show me the hint</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .probe-scene {
    position: relative;
  }
  /* Sit inside the homework window's bottom-right empty area so the
     prompt visually belongs to the homework, not floating beneath it.
     The student lines occupy the left ~50% of the paper; the bottom-
     right corner is empty space where this overlay reads naturally. */
  .probe-prompt {
    position: absolute;
    right: 18px;
    bottom: 18px;
    width: 300px;
    padding: 12px 14px;
    background: rgba(20, 20, 24, 0.96);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 216, 77, 0.40);
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 14px 36px rgba(20, 18, 12, 0.30), 0 8px 18px rgba(20, 18, 12, 0.18);
    color: white;
    font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'SF Pro Text', 'Inter Variable', Inter, sans-serif;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    line-height: 1.45;
    z-index: 4;
  }
  .prompt-q {
    color: rgba(255, 240, 200, 0.94);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .prompt-hint {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.58);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    font-size: 11.5px;
  }
  .prompt-links {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .link-mute {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.58);
    font-size: 11.5px;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: transparent;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .probe-prompt {
      right: 10px;
      bottom: 10px;
      width: 270px;
    }
  }
</style>
